I'm assuming you're referring to a cooldown timer in a game or application. I'll provide a simple example in Markdown.

**Cooldown Timer**
================

### Cooldown Timer Class

```markdown
# CooldownTimer
## Properties
* `cooldownDuration`: The duration of the cooldown in seconds.
* `startTime`: The time at which the cooldown started.
* `isOnCooldown`: A boolean indicating whether the cooldown is active.

## Methods
* `startCooldown(duration)`: Starts the cooldown with the specified duration.
* `isReady()`: Returns whether the cooldown has expired.
```

### CooldownTimer Class Implementation

```javascript
class CooldownTimer {
  constructor(cooldownDuration) {
    this.cooldownDuration = cooldownDuration;
    this.startTime = null;
    this.isOnCooldown = false;
  }

  startCooldown() {
    this.startTime = Date.now();
    this.isOnCooldown = true;
  }

  isReady() {
    if (!this.isOnCooldown) return true;
    const elapsedTime = Date.now() - this.startTime;
    return elapsedTime >= this.cooldownDuration * 1000;
  }
}
```

